  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.17.2\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nOn a fresh install with a system that does not have the vyper binary installed, compilation fails when it attempts to download the binary.\r\n```\r\nUncaught TypeError: Invalid Version: v0.3.10rc5\r\n```\r\nIt appears the `semver` dep for `hardhat-vyper` throws the above when it runs semver.eq() while searching through the version list and encountering  prerelease version string `v0.3.10rc5` which is considered to be incorrect semver.\r\n\r\nIssue is on this line:\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-vyper/src/downloader.ts#L133\r\n\r\nFixed with:\r\n```diff\r\n- semver.eq(release.tag_name, version)\r\n+ semver.eq(semver.coerce(release.tag_name).version, version)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nRun `hardhat compile` a vyper file with no vyper binaries installed in order to trigger the download..\r\n\r\nSemver will throw then running this:\r\n```\r\nsemver.eq('v0.3.10rc5', '0.3.7')\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nvyper semver download",
